author_ssm: Mark Simon Haydn, Jennifer Gargiulo, Mara Lasky, and Victoria Messana
unittitle_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Environmentalism Serials
abstract_ssm: The Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Environmentalism Serials collection groups 241 titles broadly relating to environmentalism, published between 1940 and 2004, originally received by the Tamiment Library through subscriptions, donations, and as part of archival collections. The majority of the collection consists of incomplete runs of newspapers, newsletters, magazines, and bulletins published by environmental organizations, encompassing activist networks, research bodies, conservation groups, government agencies, independent farms and co-operatives, and non-profits and charities addressing various causes. The serials provide contemporaneous coverage of a wide range of issues of concern to environmentalists, broadly addressing ecological conditions and the various threats to a stable ecosystem; featuring reports on green initiatives, legal actions, and scientific findings; and providing guidance on sustainable living. A significant quantity of the collection dates from the 1970s and 1980s, when interest in and literacy around environmental issues surged, chronicling early mainstream discourse around sustainability and climate change.
